== What Is VBAC?

_VBAC stands for Vaginal Birth After Cesarean._ It means having a vaginal delivery in a pregnancy that follows a previous cesarean birth.

_TOLAC stands for Trial of Labor After Cesarean._ This is the process of attempting vaginal birth after a previous cesarean. If you succeed, you have had a VBAC. If you need another cesarean during labor, you have had a TOLAC but not a VBAC.

_The difference matters:_ When you hear success rates for VBAC, they are measuring the percentage of women who attempt TOLAC and deliver vaginally. A 75% VBAC success rate means 75 out of 100 women who try for vaginal birth achieve it, while 25 need a repeat cesarean.

